sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant FE as Frontend
    participant MC as MediaController
    participant SS as MediaScanService
    participant FF as ffprobe
    participant MR as MediaRepository
    participant DB as SQLite<br/>(media_assets)
    participant FS as File System

    Note over U,MC: Path A — Manual scan trigger

    U->>FE: Click "Scan Directory" / enter path
    FE->>MC: POST /api/media/scan {path: "D:\\Videos"}
    MC->>SS: ScanAsync(path)

    Note over SS,DB: Phase B — Discovery & metadata extraction

    SS->>FS: Directory.EnumerateFiles(path, *.mp4|*.mov|*.avi|...)
    FS-->>SS: List of file paths

    loop For each media file
        SS->>MR: GetByFilePathAsync(filePath)
        MR-->>SS: null (new) or existing asset

        alt New file
            SS->>FF: ffprobe -print_format json -show_streams {filePath}
            FF-->>SS: {streams: [{width, height, duration, codec_name}]}
            SS->>SS: Extract metadata (mime, duration, resolution, codec)
            SS->>MR: InsertAsync(MediaAsset{...})
            MR->>DB: INSERT INTO media_assets
        else Already indexed
            SS->>SS: Skip (or update if file modified)
        end
    end

    SS-->>MC: {scanned: N, added: M, errors: E}
    MC-->>FE: 200 OK {scanned, added, errors}

    Note over FE,FS: Phase C — Catalog display & streaming

    FE->>MC: GET /api/media?query=&sort=created_at&page=1
    MC->>MR: SearchAsync(...)
    MR->>DB: SELECT ... FROM media_assets WHERE ... ORDER BY ... LIMIT ...
    DB-->>MR: rows
    MR-->>MC: (items, totalCount)
    MC-->>FE: {items: [...], page, pageSize, totalCount, totalPages}

    FE->>FE: Render MediaCard grid (catalog)

    U->>FE: Click media card
    FE->>MC: GET /api/media/{mediaId}
    MC->>MR: GetByIdAsync(mediaId)
    MR-->>MC: MediaAsset
    MC-->>FE: MediaAsset JSON

    FE->>MC: GET /api/media/{mediaId}/stream?token=...
    MC->>FS: PhysicalFile(asset.FilePath, contentType, enableRangeProcessing: true)
    FS-->>FE: Binary stream (HTTP Range supported)
    FE->>FE: Render in VideoPlayer / <img>